WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:04.254
KAI: (IN DISTANCE)
America for Americans!

00:04.338 --> 00:05.881
(CROWD WHOOPING, CHEERING)

00:05.964 --> 00:07.508
KAI: We are the wall!

00:07.591 --> 00:08.717
(WHOOPING, CHEERING)

00:08.800 --> 00:10.260
CROWD: (CHANTING) We are the wall!

00:10.344 --> 00:11.512
We are the wall!

00:11.595 --> 00:13.013
-We are the wall!
-(WEAPON COCKS)

00:13.138 --> 00:15.057
-(GUNSHOT)
-(SCREAMING, SHOUTING)

00:15.224 --> 00:17.935
(DISTORTED, ECHOING VOICES)

00:24.691 --> 00:25.692
(GUNSHOT)

00:25.776 --> 00:27.194
(SHRIEKS)

00:28.987 --> 00:30.739
-(GUNSHOT)
-(GASPS)

00:30.822 --> 00:32.741
(DISTANT, DISTORTED SCREAMS
AND SHOUTS)

00:32.824 --> 00:35.202
Run! Run!

00:37.412 --> 00:39.873
(DISTORTED SCREAMS AND SHOUTS)

00:43.377 --> 00:45.212
-(GUNSHOT)
-(SCREAMS)

00:45.295 --> 00:46.713
MAN: This is
an active shooter situation.

00:46.797 --> 00:48.966
-I have victims down. Victims down.
-No!

00:49.049 --> 00:50.634
We are moving eastbound
through the square.

00:50.717 --> 00:52.511
(SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE)

00:52.594 --> 00:55.722
(QUIETLY) Hey. Let's go. Come on.

00:55.806 --> 00:57.850
All right, c... Come on. Come on.

00:58.642 --> 01:00.018
(GRUNTS)

01:00.102 --> 01:03.522
(SHRIEKS)

01:03.605 --> 01:05.399
(IVY GASPS SOFTLY)

01:18.453 --> 01:21.999
-(SIREN WHOOPS IN DISTANCE)
-(GASPING BREATHS)

01:26.253 --> 01:27.838
-(GUNSHOT)
-(SCREAMS)

01:29.047 --> 01:30.382
MAN 1: Go. Move, move,
move, move, move.

01:30.465 --> 01:33.051
Drop the gun!

01:38.223 --> 01:40.684
-Drop the gun!
-MAN 2: Drop it! Drop the gun!

01:40.767 --> 01:43.896
-(SIREN APPROACHING)
-MAN 1: Drop it!

01:43.979 --> 01:45.814
MAN 2: Drop it! Now!

01:45.898 --> 01:48.734
-MAN 1: Drop the gun! Drop it!
-MAN 2: Now! Drop it now!

01:48.901 --> 01:51.570
MAN 1: Drop the gun.

01:51.653 --> 01:53.155
Drop the gun now.

01:53.238 --> 01:55.157
-MAN 2: Down on your knees.
-MAN 1: Let me see your hands!

01:55.240 --> 01:57.075
Let me see your hands!
Let me see your hands!

01:59.328 --> 02:01.747
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

02:05.542 --> 02:07.544
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
OVER POLICE RADIO)

02:18.180 --> 02:20.182
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:29.376 --> 03:31.962
-(ALLY SCREAMS)
-Ally, please!

03:32.045 --> 03:33.714
Please! Please help me!

03:33.797 --> 03:35.924
(CRYING) They're coming for me! Please.

03:36.800 --> 03:40.304
(PANTING) Please. Please,
the police are on their way.

03:40.387 --> 03:42.556
Please, the police
are on their way to...

03:42.639 --> 03:44.725
It's a cult, Ally.

03:44.892 --> 03:47.728
It's a sick cult,
and everyone's in it...

03:47.811 --> 03:50.814
the police, my husband,
your babysitter...

03:51.023 --> 03:52.065
your wife.

03:52.274 --> 03:53.400
No, no, please!

03:53.567 --> 03:54.943
Please, no...

03:56.153 --> 03:58.405
(PANTING)

04:00.574 --> 04:02.618
IVY: (OVER PHONE) <i>Ally.</i>

04:03.660 --> 04:05.329
<i>Hello?</i>

04:26.975 --> 04:28.810
(PHONE CHIRPING AND BUZZING)

04:37.319 --> 04:39.446
Hello?

04:39.530 --> 04:41.740
<i>Ally, this is Dr. Vincent.</i>

04:44.117 --> 04:46.203
Who told you to call me?

04:46.370 --> 04:47.788
VINCENT:
<i>I got a call from Ivy.</i>

04:47.871 --> 04:50.123
<i>You hung up on her</i>
<i>in a state of agitation.</i>

04:50.207 --> 04:52.125
<i>She's concerned about you.</i>

04:52.292 --> 04:54.837
Concerned.

04:54.920 --> 04:57.089
Right.

04:57.172 --> 05:00.717
Well, I don't know
if I can believe her anymore.

05:03.929 --> 05:05.764
I don't know who to trust.

05:05.848 --> 05:09.434
VINCENT:<i> Okay. It sounds to me</i>
<i>like you're having an episode.</i>

05:09.560 --> 05:12.062
ALLY: I am not crazy.

05:12.145 --> 05:15.941
Something is going on,
and I have been targeted.

05:17.317 --> 05:19.862
And I think Ivy
is involved, too.

05:19.945 --> 05:23.448
VINCENT: (SIGHS)<i> These are exactly</i>
<i>the kind of unfounded allegations</i>

05:23.532 --> 05:27.119
<i>that the lawyers will use</i>
<i>to take your son away.</i>

05:27.202 --> 05:30.789
<i>The best thing you</i>
<i>can do tonight is do nothing.</i>

05:30.873 --> 05:34.126
<i>Please go and get some sleep.</i>

05:34.209 --> 05:36.628
Okay.

05:36.712 --> 05:38.630
I'll do that.

05:40.424 --> 05:42.342
Good night.

06:17.294 --> 06:18.962
(RATTLING DOORKNOB)

06:20.839 --> 06:23.550
(GRUNTING, MOANING NEARBY)

06:25.385 --> 06:27.763
-(MAN 1 MOANING)
-MAN 2: Oh, yeah.

06:27.930 --> 06:30.641
(MOANING, GRUNTING)

06:37.147 --> 06:39.483
(MOANING, GRUNTING CONTINUE)

06:54.665 --> 06:56.041
(GRUNTING)

07:07.427 --> 07:08.887
-(GASPS)
-ALLY: Shh, shh, shh.

07:09.054 --> 07:10.681
Shh. Shh, shh.

07:15.394 --> 07:18.272
-(WHISPERS) Ow. Ow. Ow.
-Shh, shh, shh.

07:20.816 --> 07:22.943
ALLY: (WHISPERS) Okay.

07:23.110 --> 07:24.403
Okay.

07:25.654 --> 07:27.072
Come on.

07:27.239 --> 07:29.449
Okay. Come on, turn around.
Can you walk?

07:29.658 --> 07:30.909
Get up.

07:31.076 --> 07:34.121
-I need you to stay close.
-MEADOW: Yes. Okay.

07:34.288 --> 07:35.914
Okay.

07:36.248 --> 07:39.251
-(MEADOW WHIMPERS)
-Fucking bitch.

07:40.878 --> 07:43.130
(MECHANICAL WHIRRING)

07:46.675 --> 07:48.677
-(WOMEN SHRIEK)
-(SCREAMING)

07:53.640 --> 07:55.726
Run!

07:55.893 --> 07:58.395
(CAR ALARM CHIRPING)

08:00.731 --> 08:03.734
-(ENGINE STARTS)
-(TIRES SQUEALING)

08:13.160 --> 08:16.079
(ALARM BLARING)

08:21.376 --> 08:23.670
-Hello?
-(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

08:23.754 --> 08:26.256
MEADOW: What are we doing here?

08:27.341 --> 08:29.343
Oh, can I have a cappuccino?

08:29.426 --> 08:31.345
ALLY: Would you just be quiet, please?

08:31.512 --> 08:33.680
Can't hear myself think.

08:35.349 --> 08:36.892
(ALARM STOPS)

08:39.561 --> 08:42.272
ALLY: We can't just
keep driving around.

08:42.356 --> 08:44.900
We're dark on Mondays,
so we should be fine here,

08:44.983 --> 08:46.693
at least until we figure out
our next move.

08:46.777 --> 08:48.570
No. No, no, no.
We need to keep going.

08:48.654 --> 08:51.323
We need to get out of the state,
maybe even out of this country.

08:51.406 --> 08:53.200
Why don't you clean yourself up?

08:53.283 --> 08:55.077
And then sit down.

08:59.540 --> 09:01.208
Listen to me.

09:01.375 --> 09:03.877
I am not going anywhere
without my son.

09:05.420 --> 09:06.880
You don't want me
to take you to the police,

09:06.964 --> 09:08.549
you say they're in on it, fine.

09:08.632 --> 09:11.760
But you need to tell me
what the hell is going on here.

09:11.844 --> 09:14.054
You used the word "cult."

09:14.137 --> 09:16.807
-You said my wife was involved.
-She is.

09:26.441 --> 09:27.943
Convince me.

09:28.986 --> 09:31.029
-(CHUCKLES) Really?
-Yeah, really.

09:31.113 --> 09:32.364
Convince you?

09:32.573 --> 09:34.658
What's it gonna take, lady?

09:34.825 --> 09:37.411
How do you think we've been
getting into your house?

09:38.787 --> 09:40.163
What do you mean?

09:40.414 --> 09:42.875
Okay. Uh, like the night
of the guinea pig.

09:42.958 --> 09:45.502
Ivy made sure the alarm
at your house was off

09:45.586 --> 09:47.087
and that the door was unlocked,

09:47.171 --> 09:49.256
and she texted us
when you were a few blocks away.

09:50.257 --> 09:52.301
I don't believe you.

09:52.384 --> 09:53.969
Why would she do that?

09:54.344 --> 09:55.971
To make you crazy.

09:56.054 --> 09:58.765
(LAUGHS) Why would my own wife
want to make me crazy?

09:58.974 --> 10:01.268
You have to ask her that,
but she wasn't super thrilled

10:01.351 --> 10:03.395
you voted for Jill Stein,
I know that much.

10:03.562 --> 10:04.730
Are you kidding me?

10:04.813 --> 10:06.148
That's not a reason.

10:06.315 --> 10:08.775
Maybe she just hates you.
I don't know.

10:08.859 --> 10:11.612
But you were just one project,
we had a bunch.

10:11.737 --> 10:14.323
You know all those dead birds
that you found on your lawn?

10:14.406 --> 10:16.617
We did that all over the city.

10:16.783 --> 10:18.327
And there was nothing
in those trucks.

10:18.410 --> 10:19.661
They were water trucks.

10:20.370 --> 10:22.664
We killed the birds
by poisoning our feeders.

10:23.248 --> 10:25.959
-Why?
-To make people paranoid.

10:26.126 --> 10:28.378
To scare them
and to soften them up.

10:28.462 --> 10:29.838
ALLY: For what?

10:31.006 --> 10:32.132
The takeover.

10:33.717 --> 10:35.511
This is insane.

10:36.094 --> 10:38.222
I... am <i>not </i>insane.

10:38.430 --> 10:40.807
This... This is insane.

10:42.601 --> 10:45.437
My wife is not
in a fucking cult!

10:45.521 --> 10:47.856
Ivy's not the type.
She's not a joiner.

10:47.940 --> 10:49.816
She hates all organized religion.

10:49.900 --> 10:52.236
She doesn't believe in anything.

10:52.819 --> 10:54.780
That's kind of how it starts.

10:54.863 --> 10:57.241
If you already believed in something,

10:57.324 --> 11:00.285
there wouldn't be any room for <i>him.</i>

11:00.369 --> 11:01.828
ALLY: Him?

11:03.121 --> 11:04.706
Him who?

11:04.873 --> 11:06.917
(ON TELEVISION) <i>This is Beverly Hope,</i>

11:07.084 --> 11:09.586
<i>coming to you from City Hall</i>
<i>where any moment,</i>

11:09.670 --> 11:11.088
<i>candidates for city council</i>

11:11.171 --> 11:12.923
<i>will have their final opportunity</i>

11:13.006 --> 11:15.926
<i>to address the terrified</i>
<i>citizens of Brookfield Heights.</i>

11:16.093 --> 11:19.346
<i>With the election days away,</i>
<i>front-runner Kai Anderson,</i>

11:19.429 --> 11:21.223
<i>-continues to soar in the polls...</i>
-MEADOW: There he is.

11:21.306 --> 11:23.642
<i>...with an unprecedented 16-point lead.</i>

11:23.809 --> 11:25.894
Oh, my God, I know him.

11:26.061 --> 11:27.688
MEADOW: Not as well as he knows you.

11:27.855 --> 11:30.566
He's the one who got
the protesters to leave that day.

11:30.649 --> 11:33.193
It's because he paid them
to be there.

11:34.528 --> 11:37.239
What? They're...
They're all members of the cult?

11:37.364 --> 11:38.365
MEADOW: No.

11:38.740 --> 11:41.201
You can't just join it
like it's the AARP.

11:41.285 --> 11:42.828
He has to choose you.

11:46.582 --> 11:48.625
(QUIETLY) Who's your favorite Housewife?

11:48.709 --> 11:51.211
Oh, let me think,
my favorite Housewife is probably...

11:51.378 --> 11:54.631
MEADOW: <i>I'd been in love with</i>
<i>Harrison since I was ten,</i>

11:54.798 --> 11:58.760
<i>but I never knew what love was</i>
<i>until I met Kai.</i>

11:58.927 --> 12:02.139
HARRISON: Yeah.

12:02.222 --> 12:04.141
(MEADOW GASPS)

12:05.851 --> 12:08.228
Is there anything you can't do?

12:08.353 --> 12:09.813
It's not finished.

12:09.897 --> 12:13.150
Um, I still have to shade this in
and add some definition here.

12:14.651 --> 12:16.528
KAI: It's beautiful.

12:16.695 --> 12:18.947
It's everything I ever wanted.

12:19.031 --> 12:20.824
You're just being nice.

12:20.908 --> 12:23.410
I'm not.

12:24.244 --> 12:25.579
You're incredible.

12:25.662 --> 12:28.415
You have blown
my every expectation.

12:28.582 --> 12:30.667
I know I've asked a lot.

12:31.877 --> 12:35.422
But a larva bee has to shed
its skin to become the queen.

12:35.589 --> 12:37.716
It can be painful,

12:37.799 --> 12:40.969
but the dark must prevail
to bring forth the light.

12:41.136 --> 12:44.056
And you...

12:44.139 --> 12:47.059
burn brighter than anyone.

12:47.226 --> 12:48.477
MEADOW: <i>When Kai looked at me,</i>

12:48.560 --> 12:49.853
<i>it was better than a Xanny high.</i>

12:49.937 --> 12:51.313
<i>It was better than sex.</i>

12:51.396 --> 12:53.148
<i>He made me feel special,</i>

12:53.232 --> 12:55.817
<i>like we were the only</i>
<i>two people in the world.</i>

12:55.984 --> 12:58.237
<i>I'd been afraid for so long.</i>

12:58.320 --> 13:01.156
<i>I'd built up a wall</i>
<i>of Housewives and Drag Races</i>

13:01.240 --> 13:04.826
<i>to anesthetize myself from</i>
<i>all the shit in the world.</i>

13:04.910 --> 13:07.204
<i>But I hated feeling helpless.</i>

13:07.287 --> 13:09.456
<i>Hated myself for being so weak,</i>

13:09.540 --> 13:12.376
<i>trapped by feminist expectations.</i>

13:12.459 --> 13:14.711
<i>Every day faced with the failure</i>

13:14.795 --> 13:17.548
<i>that I wasn't a successful boss bitch,</i>

13:17.631 --> 13:19.007
<i>that I had no loving husband</i>

13:19.174 --> 13:22.845
<i>and 2.5 kids at home to bake</i>
<i>a goddamn casserole for,</i>

13:22.928 --> 13:25.764
<i>that I was nowhere near</i>
<i>having it all.</i>

13:25.848 --> 13:29.810
<i>And this rage began</i>
<i>to build and fester and burn,</i>

13:29.893 --> 13:33.272
<i>until Kai finally set me free.</i>

13:38.360 --> 13:40.571
<i>He made me feel invincible.</i>

13:40.654 --> 13:41.822
(KAI WHOOPS)

13:41.947 --> 13:43.365
You almost cut his goddamn head off.

13:43.448 --> 13:44.700
(BOTH LAUGH)

13:44.783 --> 13:46.702
You're amazing.

13:48.996 --> 13:51.540
MEADOW: <i>Together we were unstoppable.</i>

13:51.623 --> 13:53.542
(ENGINE STARTS)

13:56.461 --> 13:58.172
KAI: I know I've asked a lot,

13:58.255 --> 14:02.176
but a larva bee has to shed
its skin to become the queen.

14:02.259 --> 14:04.219
It can be painful,

14:04.303 --> 14:07.514
but the dark must prevail
to bring forth the light.

14:07.598 --> 14:09.975
And you, Ivy,

14:10.184 --> 14:12.436
burn brighter than anyone.

14:17.983 --> 14:19.860
(PANTING)

14:24.489 --> 14:25.699
What are you doing?

14:25.908 --> 14:27.743
I'm leaving.

14:27.910 --> 14:29.661
I need you, Meadow.

14:29.828 --> 14:31.622
We are so close to getting
everything we want.

14:31.788 --> 14:34.166
No, everything <i>you </i>want.

14:34.333 --> 14:37.377
You are so full of shit.

14:38.295 --> 14:39.838
I loved you.

14:40.797 --> 14:42.466
I'm out.

14:46.637 --> 14:49.056
(SIGHS) Will you open your eyes?

14:49.223 --> 14:52.434
I mean, seriously, is Kai the idiot?

14:52.601 --> 14:54.144
Or is it us for believing

14:54.228 --> 14:56.104
that any of this shit
was gonna work?

14:56.522 --> 14:57.940
(MEADOW EXHALES)

14:59.316 --> 15:01.193
Can I just ask you a question?

15:01.276 --> 15:03.779
When's the last time a seat
on the zoning board

15:03.862 --> 15:07.115
led to world domination?
I mean, think about it.

15:07.282 --> 15:09.201
No one outside this Podunk town

15:09.284 --> 15:11.745
even knows who the hell you are.

15:12.621 --> 15:13.789
The whole thing would be hilarious

15:13.914 --> 15:16.959
if it wasn't so insane. (SHORT CHUCKLE)

15:17.125 --> 15:18.502
KAI: Harrison.

15:18.585 --> 15:20.546
I think it's time to call the police.

15:22.422 --> 15:24.508
Something terrible
has happened to your wife.

15:25.425 --> 15:27.636
-(MEADOW WHIMPERS)
-(GRUNTS)

15:28.136 --> 15:29.179
Ow.

15:31.598 --> 15:35.352
(MEADOW PANTS AND CRIES)

15:38.689 --> 15:40.315
A cat goes missing,

15:40.482 --> 15:42.985
and there are posters plastered
all over the city.

15:43.151 --> 15:46.738
But you, no one's even
noticed you're gone.

15:46.905 --> 15:50.284
No one gives a shit
if you live or die.

15:50.450 --> 15:52.494
(CRYING)

15:55.330 --> 15:56.915
Leave us.

16:01.420 --> 16:04.047
(MEADOW PANTS)

16:13.015 --> 16:14.933
You're worthless.

16:17.519 --> 16:19.855
-You don't exist.
-(MEADOW WHIMPERS)

16:25.277 --> 16:27.654
KAI: You're nothing.

16:27.863 --> 16:29.031
(GASPS)

16:35.704 --> 16:37.331
(EXHALES)

16:39.082 --> 16:42.127
-No regrets?
-Fuck her.

16:43.545 --> 16:45.714
MEADOW: <i>I'd be dead</i>
<i>if you hadn't found me.</i>

16:45.881 --> 16:48.258
If the cops in this town
won't listen,

16:48.342 --> 16:49.968
we will go to the next town,

16:50.135 --> 16:52.054
-or to the FBI.
-MEADOW: No, you don't understand.

16:52.262 --> 16:54.389
There is no one who can help us.

16:54.473 --> 16:56.975
No one will listen.
You know that.

16:57.059 --> 16:59.520
There is only one way
to stop him.

17:01.063 --> 17:02.981
We have to kill him.

17:09.947 --> 17:12.824
KAI: <i>Friends! Please, please.</i>

17:12.991 --> 17:15.452
The federal government
is now run by people

17:15.536 --> 17:17.162
who believe, as I do,

17:17.329 --> 17:20.415
that a real change has to happen
on the local level!

17:20.582 --> 17:23.126
-(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)
-CROWD: Yes! Yes!

17:25.170 --> 17:27.756
Washington, D.C.
is not gonna save you

17:27.840 --> 17:29.007
when the bogeyman comes.

17:29.216 --> 17:31.635
And mark my words,
he not only will come,

17:31.718 --> 17:33.637
he has come to our little hamlet.

17:33.846 --> 17:35.180
-The monsters are here.
-(CROWD REACTS)

17:35.264 --> 17:36.849
It's time to be scared.

17:37.015 --> 17:38.600
WOMAN: Bullshit.

17:41.311 --> 17:42.729
Excuse me, ma'am?

17:42.813 --> 17:44.648
Could you stand up
for all of us, please?

17:46.191 --> 17:48.861
-And state your name.
-Sally Keffler.

17:49.570 --> 17:51.989
Ms. Keffler, you have a problem
with something I'm saying.

17:52.614 --> 17:54.658
I think you're a snake oil salesman.

17:54.908 --> 17:57.286
-(KAI LAUGHS, SCATTERED LAUGHTER IN CROWD)
-And not even a very good one.

17:58.370 --> 17:59.621
-(CROWD REACTS)
-So...

17:59.746 --> 18:01.999
there haven't been a series
of horrible murders

18:02.082 --> 18:03.625
over the past month or so,

18:03.709 --> 18:06.503
including the brutal slaying
of Councilman Chang.

18:07.588 --> 18:09.423
And I wasn't beaten up
by a gang of illegals.

18:09.506 --> 18:10.674
WOMAN: Yeah.

18:10.757 --> 18:12.676
And Bob Thompson's satanic murder

18:12.759 --> 18:15.554
-wasn't broadcast on television.
-Overall crime

18:15.637 --> 18:17.723
is down 14% from last year,

18:17.890 --> 18:20.058
and almost 30% from 1980.

18:21.268 --> 18:23.729
We need to get serious
about finding whoever's responsible

18:23.812 --> 18:26.273
for the crimes you're
talking about, but...

18:27.399 --> 18:30.027
(SCOFFS) you're just trying
to make these people scared.

18:30.235 --> 18:31.653
You're damn right I am.

18:31.737 --> 18:33.488
Scared is what is
gonna keep them safe.

